external_knowledge:
- Mortality rate is a measure of the number of deaths (due to a specific disease) per 100,000 people per year.
- Average mortality rate > 1.0 implies that the disease has a significant impact on the population; 
- Total cases > 100 ensures that the statistics are based on a substantial number of cases, making them more reliable.

